"{\"uid\": \"latimes.com-california-story-2024-04-26-lax-plans-to-update-terminal-and-gate-numbers-ahead-of-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles International Airporthas designated $43 million to improve the way travelers navigate the airport, which will include a renumbering of terminals, gates and stations ahead of the 2028 Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9734221245789699, \"rank\": 0.027303540792227077, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The project will focus on how travelers get from terminal to terminal, gate to gate and move between the upcomingAutomated People Mover, rental car facility and parking lots.\", \"from\": 206, \"to\": 380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_mover\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.221403296899238e-21, \"text\": \"People Mover\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_mover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_mover\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Board of Airport Commissioners voted earlier this month to award Webcor Construction $23.9 million for the design and construction of a new \\\"wayfinding system\\\" that would update airport signage.\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Webster-Chicago\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Webcor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Webster-Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Webster-Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The specific cost of construction and implementation has not yet been determined.\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"California  A strained relationship between LAX and the People Mover contractor has led to project delays, according to credit agency Fitch Ratings.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 664, \"end\": 674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5100309282957578e-13, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 708, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.812609653853264e-27, \"text\": \"LAX\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\"}, {\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_mover\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.221403296899238e-21, \"text\": \"People Mover\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_mover\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/People_mover\"}, {\"begin\": 798, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitch_Ratings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fitch Ratings\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitch_Ratings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fitch_Ratings\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A perfect journey is when one does not get lost,\\\" Hans Thilenius, deputy executive director of the Terminal Development and Improvement Program, said at a recent board meeting.\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The project is expected to be finished by 2027, Thilenius said.\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The intention is to offer an \\\"accessible, clear, consistent\\\" way to get around the sprawling airport, according to theproposal.\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Webcor's proposal includes a consolidation of some terminals by name: Terminal 1 and Concourse 0 would become Terminal 1; Terminals 2 and 3 would become Terminal 2; Terminal B, which includes  the Midfield Satellite Concourse South and the Bradley West Gates would become Tom Bradley Terminal 3; and Terminals 7 and 8 would become Terminal 7.\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Webster-Chicago\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Webcor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Webster-Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Webster-Chicago\"}, {\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Midfield\", \"score\": 0.965042330150868, \"rank\": 0.0362239756297489, \"text\": \"Midfield\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Midfield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Midfield\"}, {\"begin\": 1402, \"end\": 1411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concourse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.051126609458002e-18, \"text\": \"Concourse\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concourse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Concourse\"}, {\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Bradley_(American_politician)\", \"score\": 0.9873413659671255, \"rank\": 0.005492362690934138, \"text\": \"Tom Bradley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Bradley_(American_politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Bradley_(American_politician)\"}, {\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terminals_of_Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"score\": 0.9999999999899956, \"rank\": 9.26574574743086e-12, \"text\": \"Terminal 3\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terminals_of_Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Terminals_of_Los_Angeles_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The proposal also includes a new gate numbering system that would designate specific letters to specific terminals instead of thecurrent overlapping system: Terminal 1 would  have Gates A and B; Terminal 2 would have Gates C and D; Terminal 3 would  have Gates E and F; Terminal 4 would  have Gate G; Terminal 5 would have Gate H; Terminal 6 would  have Gate J; Terminal 7 would  have Gates K and L, and Terminal 8 would have Gate M.  \\\"No final decision has yet been made regarding the numbering of terminals, gates and stations,\\\"  said  LAX development projects' director of communications Jessica Merritt.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2121, \"end\": 2128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Simpson\", \"score\": 0.999252937222673, \"rank\": 0.0006308671102527906, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Simpson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Simpson\"}, {\"begin\": 2129, \"end\": 2136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merritt_Parkway\", \"score\": 0.9999999184624391, \"rank\": 6.440326465757068e-08, \"text\": \"Merritt\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merritt_Parkway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Merritt_Parkway\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That will be decided during the design phase, with a focus on ensuring a holistic and initiative wayfinding strategy for the airport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2138, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"California  Saying it's unfair that Clear customers can cut TSA security lines, a California state senator wants to require the company to operate a separate line.\", \"from\": 2275, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5100309282957578e-13, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 2335, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transportation_Security_Administration\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.087798319471235e-34, \"text\": \"TSA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transportation_Security_Administration\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transportation_Security_Administration\"}, {\"begin\": 2357, \"end\": 2367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5100309282957578e-13, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The project will rely on user-testing by airlines, customers and employees, Thilenius said.\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Roughly 50 to 75 people have  tried out the possible new gate renumbering system.\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The system will also focus on  customers' reliance on technology to help people get around the airport through the use of smart devices such as mobile phones and watches and with consideration to language and accessibility for those who are hearing- or vision-impaired.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several projects to renovate terminals, improve security checkpoints and enhance accessibility to and from the airport are  underway at LAX, which saw about6.3 million passengerslast month.\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 3075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3022, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.812609653853264e-27, \"text\": \"LAX\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These include a $1.6-billion project to update Terminals 4 and 5; a $477.5-million project to extend Terminal 1 and a $230-million project to improve Terminal 6 - all part of a $30-billion overhaul at the world's fifth-busiest airport.\", \"from\": 3077, \"to\": 3312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Us  Colleen Shalby is a reporter for the Los Angeles Times covering transportation and mobility, as well as post-Eaton fire rebuilding efforts.\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3362, \"end\": 3379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.132345036753328e-24, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She previously wrote about education and breaking news throughout California.\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3531, \"end\": 3541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5100309282957578e-13, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was part of the team that was a 2020 Pulitzer Prize finalist for coverage of a dive-boat fire off the Santa Barbara coast.\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3649, \"end\": 3662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Barbara_Unified_School_District\", \"score\": 0.999999999487045, \"rank\": 5.03364962939966e-10, \"text\": \"Santa Barbara\",